    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.48/1857.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Shall we repatriate John Keller with family of seven and other destitute
                    Americans soliciting free transportation to United States and who had ample
                    opportunity during time Department maintained chartered ships but refused to
                    go?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
